scussion has been misunderstood. Either go ontu Twitter and read the whole =\r\ndiscussion point by point, or simple ignore it and keep doing your own stuf=\r\nf.=C2=A0 \n=C2=A0 \n-Regards \n=C2=A0Rajarshi \n=C2=A0 \n\n=C2=A0 \nBazeecha-e-atf=\r\nal hain duniya mere aage. \nHota hain shab-o-roz tamasha mere aage \n=C2=A0 \n=\r\nEk khel hain aurang-e-sulemaan mere nazdeek \nEk baat hain ijaz-e-masiah mer=\r\ne aage. \n\n\n\n___________________________________ \n\nFrom: Narasimha PVR Rao &lt;=\r\npvr@...&gt; \nTo: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com \nSent: Mon, 1 August, 20=\r\n11 7:18:11 AM \nSubject: [vedic-wisdom] On Siddhis & Spiritual Progress \n\n=\r\n=C2=A0 \nNamaste friends, \n=C2=A0 \nThis is a small writeup on &quot;siddhis&quot; vis-=\r\na-vis spiritual progress, in reaction to further exchanges on Twitter. This=\r\n is a delicate area where many have misconceptions and I will try to addres=\r\ns them. \n=C2=A0 \n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n=C2=A0 \nMaharshi Vasishtha&#39;s teaching to =\r\nLord Rama is clear in Yoga Vaasishtham. The goal of existence and sadhana i=\r\ns self-realization. Siddhis are to be neither specifically sought nor speci=\r\nfically avoided, by a seeker of Self. If Nature gives one some siddhi(s), o=\r\nne should accept them with neither excitement nor disappointment. But one s=\r\nhould NOT run after them, for they are neither necessary nor sufficient for=\r\n self-realization and liberation. \n=C2=A0 \nVivekananda used the same princi=\r\nple when Ramakirishna proposed to give his siddhis to Vivekananda. He asked=\r\n whether the siddhis will enable him to realize god. Ramakrishna said no. V=\r\nivekananda firmly declined the offer then! Of course, when Ramakrishna gave=\r\n them anyway later, he accepted them. Vivekananda&#39;s two actions demonstrate=\r\n Vasishtha&#39;s instructions well. \n=C2=A0 \n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n=C2=A0 \nLet us use=\r\n the analogy of climbing a hill. Climbing hill is one&#39;s spiritual sadhana. =\r\nReaching the top is liberation. Different people climb the hill from differ=\r\nent sides and using different paths. There may be trees with nice fruits on=\r\n the sides of the road. They are siddhis or special abilities. \n=C2=A0 \nIf =\r\none gets distracted, starts climbing the trees and collecting fruits, one&#39;s=\r\n journey gets delayed and one may not reach the top. That is why Vasishtha =\r\nsays a seeker of Self does not pursue any siddhis. \n=C2=A0 \nBut if some fru=\r\nits fall in one&#39;s lap by themselves, one can keep them. Similarly, siddhis =\r\nthat come to one by themselves can be accepted by a seeker of Self. \n=C2=A0=\r\n \nNow an important distinction: \n=C2=A0 \nThere are some trees that are foun=\r\nd at lower altitudes also, but some really special trees are found at very =\r\nhigh altitudes only. If one has such a fruit, it shows that one has climbed=\r\n great heights. Similarly, some siddhis do not mean much, but some siddhis =\r\nare very special and only really elevated sadhakas can obtain them (whether=\r\n by trying or without trying). If a sadhakas demonstrates such a siddhi, yo=\r\nu can see that one progressed a lot. However, the key is that one who climb=\r\ned the same or more distance may not have that or any other fruit. \n=C2=A0 =\r\n\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n=C2=A0 \nUnlike in the example of climbing hill, which is=\r\n an external activity, spiritual progress in real life is *internal*. There=\r\n is NO way for anyone to know for sure how much progress one has made, how =\r\nmuch self-control one has internally and what exactly goes on in one&#39;s mind=\r\n. We may try to judge it from external factors such as actions, words etc, =\r\nbut it is not necessarily accurate. \n=C2=A0 \nHere, some people swayed by si=\r\nddhis may be tempted to use one&#39;s siddhis to judge how high one climbed. Bu=\r\nt that is faulty. One person who reached the absolute top may not have any =\r\nfruits, while one person who still has ways to climb may have gotten some r=\r\neally nice fruit. Using externaslly demonstrable siddhis that are neither n=\r\necessary nor sufficient for Self-realization as a measure of one&#39;s progress=\r\n is unsound. \n=C2=A0 \nGiven that spiritual progress is internal, how can we=\r\n judge it and compare people then? Well, we need not and should not. Only a=\r\n sarvaantaryaami - a perfected being who has access to each being&#39;s interna=\r\nl state - can do that. \n=C2=A0 \n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n=C2=A0 \nRajarshi, you are a=\r\nssuming that Ramakrishna Paramahamsa is a Paramahamsa on Vimalananda&#39;s scal=\r\ne. You are concluding that Ramakrishna is a Paramahamsa; Abhedananda, Vivek=\r\nananda etc are lower than that; Vimalananda is a rishi; and hence Vimalanan=\r\nda is superior to Abhedananda and Vivekananda by 2pwr16 to 2. \n=C2=A0 \nIs P=\r\naramahamsa Nithyananda, who was caught in a sex scandal, also a Paramahamsa=\r\n because he is known so? See, how people are famously known may or may not =\r\nreflect their spiritual stature. Real spiritual stature is internal and you=\r\n cannot see it. \n=C2=A0 \nWe do not know who Ramakrishna Paramahamsa really =\r\nis. He may not be just a paramahamsa on Vimalananda&#39;s scale, but be a siddh=\r\na or a natha or even a rishi. He may even be Vishnu himself, as he himself =\r\nsaid and some religious experts of that time declared based on various sign=\r\ns. If Ramakrishna Paramahamsa is Vishnu himself, Vivekananda, Abhedananda e=\r\ntc can definitely be rishis or naths in Vimalananda&#39;s scale. If your argume=\r\nnt is that they cannot be because they did not demonstrate siddhis compatib=\r\nle with that status, that is a non-point as I explained above. The disagree=\r\nment between then boils down a difference in the relevance and importance o=\r\nf externally demonstrated siddhis. \n=C2=A0 \n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * \n=C2=A0 \nWhy thi=\r\ns is relevant and I spent some time on this is that some people seem to hav=\r\ne misconceptions. The take home for some people from some books describing =\r\nmiracles and siddhis may be that siddhis are important. \n=C2=A0 \nVasishtha =\r\nis not only a rishi, but one of saptarshis. Please read what he taught Lord=\r\n Rama in Yoga Vaasishtham. It is the essence of Veda and Upanishad. It will=\r\n balance your views and mould your attitude. Read Yoga Vaasishtham. Siddhis=\r\n are neither necessary nor sufficient for self-realization. Don&#39;t be distra=\r\ncted by them or be infatuated with them. \n=C2=A0 \nThe goal of sadhana is th=\r\nat your notions of &quot;this is I and these are mine&quot; get subtler and subtler a=\r\nnd hold of six internal enemies on you becomes weaker and weaker. Others ma=\r\ny or may not be able to see and judge your progress, but you know your prog=\r\nress and weaknesses the best. THAT is the crux and siddhis have no relevanc=\r\ne or meaning. Any fascination for them will set you back in your sadhana. \n=\r\n=C2=A0 \nBest regards, \nNarasimha \n-----------------------------------------=\r\n-------------------------- \n=C2=A0 Free Jyotish Software, Free Jyotish Less=\r\nons, Jyotish Writings, \n&quot;Do It Yourself&quot; ritual manuals for short Homam and=\r\n Pitri Tarpana: \n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 http://www.VedicAstrologer.or=\r\ng \n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 Films that make a difference: http://SaraswatiF=\r\nilms.org \n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 Spirituality: http://groups.yahoo.com/gr=\r\noup/vedic-wisdom \n=C2=A0 Jyotish writings: http://groups.yahoo.com/group/Jy=\r\notish