ee forever after that. Vimalananda, on \n&gt; the other h=\r\nand, had atleast one more birth clearly as he said a body was \n&gt; waiting fo=\r\nr him. That way, forget about &quot;RK&#39;s discples put togtr&quot;, just \n&gt; Abhedanand=\r\na alone is superior to Vimalananda! \n&gt; \n&gt; Again, please note that this is j=\r\nust one definition. One can have many \n&gt; definitions. The key is not to jum=\r\np to unwise conclusions on any \n&gt; hierarchies and say that &quot;X is weightier =\r\nthan Y and so what he said must \n&gt; be more correct&quot;. \n&gt; \n&gt; People with lops=\r\nided understanding of scriptures take relative knowledge \n&gt; to be absolute =\r\nand jump to unwise conclusions. I am afraid some people \n&gt; are doing the sa=\r\nme now with &quot;modern scriptures&quot; such as the Aghora \n&gt; books. Don&#39;t fall int=\r\no the trap of taking something as gospel or as \n&gt; absolute. Written words a=\r\nre always relative and never absolute. \n&gt; Discriminate relative knowledge u=\r\nsing intellect at first and hopefully \n&gt; using experencial realization late=\r\nr on. \n&gt; \n&gt; More importantly, while we are still searching for &quot;maturity&quot;, =\r\nwe should \n&gt; not commit the &quot;error&quot; of making negative judgmental comments =\r\nof greats \n&gt; who did far more sadhana than us and experienced a lot more th=\r\nan us. \n&gt; ------------------------------- \n&gt; \n&gt; Best regards, \n&gt; Narasimha =\r\n\n \r\n--0-1652936880-1312424755=:76107\r\nContent-Type: text/html; charset=utf-8\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\n\r\n&lt;html&gt;&lt;body&gt;&lt;div style=3D&quot;color:#000; background-color:#fff; font-family:ti=\r\nmes new roman, new york, times, serif;font-size:12pt&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;Namaste,&lt;/=\r\nspan&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;Since these discussions c=\r\nentered a lot on Swami Vivekananda and